          "Extacted using EFD",
          "Time is often not considered in models for KT in either self-paced or tutor-based education -time to be understood as time elapsed between sequential events.",
          "T-LSTM introduce the ability to model time intervals and incorporate into the prediction",
          "Students who had requested hints were eliminated from the sample.\n\nCode traces are timestamped snapshots of student code.\n\nFeatures are extracted using a form of AutoML called Expert Feature Detector.\n\n",
          "ZeroR,\nLogistic Regression, \nRecent Temporal Pattern,\nLTSM,\nT-LSTM\n",
          "Prefix Split",
          "First 6 Minutes \n\n{Accuracy: 0.7658 - T-LSTM, Precision: 0.875 - T-LSTM, Recall: 0.8429 - RTP, F1-Score: 0.7778 - T-LSTM, AUC: 0.7528 - T-LSTM}\n\nAfter 20 minutes\n\n{AUC: 0.7512 - T-LSTM}",
          "BKT was not considered for this open-ended task since there are no specific knowledge components or predefined steps that need to be followed.\n\nTask on iSNAP is defined by the learners being able to solve a homework: a snapshop of their screen is taken every 2 minutes and this sequence is used for prediction.",
          "Only a single modeling task per learning environment.\n\nSmall sample size.\n\nNo alternative methods to assess time-awareness.\n"
