    {
      "id": "1914750c-f3ba-8089-a9a7-c69917f7e286",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Some of the most well known methods for KT are BKT and LSTMs. The problem with these approaches is that sub-divide time into discrete time-steps and not continuous. However, time between events  varies significantly and, fot that reason, authors decide to use Time-Aware LSTM for KT. ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "1914750c-f3ba-8089-a9a7-c69917f7e286",
        "parent": {
          "type": "page_id",
          "page_id": "18c4750c-f3ba-8088-bbb5-e82aee13cbcd"
        },
        "created_time": "2025-02-05T19:11:00.000Z",
        "last_edited_time": "2025-02-05T19:15:00.000Z",
        "created_by": {
